commit.message: improve detection of Microsoft Visual C binary resource files (from pali)
Cantralize coff handling (Joerg Jenderek)
Better support for SGI images (Joerg Jenderek)
Fix clear example (Luke Shumaker)
better explanation for ne (from pali)

Diff detect 32-bit Watcom Win386 extender based
application in 16-bit Windows 3.x NE binaries (from pali)
Detect 16-bit Windows 3.x NE P-code application (from pali)
Suppress warnings instead of exiting.

Fix the version recognition of combined ISO + UDF images and
the recognition of images with blocksize above 2048 bytes. Add a
comment explaining why (even the improved) recognition is imprecise (pali)
Add linux perf (Ben Dooks)
Add magic for Microsoft_Advisor_Help (Joerg Jenderek)
shows running mode also for Windows 3.0 NE binaries. (pali)
Add c64 cartridges (Joerg Jenderek)
Detect CauseWay 3P binaries (pali)

Improvements in detection of NE 5 binaries with unspecified OS type (0).
Lot of NE OS/2 binaries in MS OS/2 SDK are of such type, so when detection
fails prints generic string: "for OS/2 1.x or MS Windows 1.x/2.x"
(instead of the current just "for MS Windows") (pali)
Improvements for Adobe FrameMaker (Joerg Jenderek)
PR/504: skissane: Recognise z/OS Program Objects
PR/506: Martin: detect APNG images
PR/503: marcoxa: fix indirect offset documentation bugs
Add support for c64 tape images (Joerg Jenderek)
consistently use iX86 for intel processors (pali)

Differentiate between pdp, mmdf, and targa to recognize C64 disk
images (Joerg Jenderek)

Prints name of the executable (extender or DPMI host) which is autoloaded and
check for structure sizes to prevent out-of-bound read (pali)
add more coff binaries (pali)
Recognize signatures of other DOS extenders (IGC XMLOD, CauseWay and D3X) (pali)

Recognize COFF object files which can be created by MS CL.EXE compilers
for different architectures (pali)

Magdir/epoc: add some more MIME types

Also fix some errors, using the information in plptools:

https://github.com/rrthomas/plptools

Note that the information will now be removed from plptools, and further
clarification should be sought at the URL in the epoc file.
Add powerpc (pali)
add and centralize coff handling (pali)

Recognize MS-DOS EXP Phar Lap binaries (MP, P2 and P3 formats) used
by Phar Lap 286 and 386 DOS extenders. (pali)
